  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "SA-LOAM (Li et al. 2021) is a semantic-aided LiDAR SLAM method with loop closure detection.",
    "It leverages a semantic-assisted ICP, including semantic matching, downsampling, and planar constraint, and integrates a semantic graphbased place recognition method in the loop closure detection module.",
    "SA-LOAM exploits semantic information to improve the accuracy of point cloud registration and designs a semantic-graph-based loop closure detection module to eliminate the accumulated error.",
    "To leverage the spatial relations of internal structures for place recognition, Gong et al. (2021) presented a two-level framework based on a spatial relation graph.",
    "The framework first segments the 3D point cloud into multiple clusters, then extracts features from each cluster and the spatial relation descriptors between clusters to represent the 3D point cloud scene."
  ],
